SOUTH AFRICA DAYBOOK: February Trade Deficit, Central Bank's Gill Marcus

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-03-29T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/south-africa-daybook-february-trade-deficit-central-bank-s-gill-marcus.html
South Africa  will post a trade
deficit of 1.5 billion rand ($218.4 million) in February, a
second month of shortfalls, according to the median estimate of
eight analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  Estimates for the data, which will be released at 2 p.m. in
Johannesburg by the South African Revenue Service, ranged from a
5.1 billion-rand deficit to a 2 billion-rand surplus.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro in Johannesburg at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at   vwessels@bloomberg.net . 